results.description:
My wife and I went to Denver for our honeymoon.  While on a hike with friends, we went off the trail to get back to our car.  On our way, we saw this fawn resting and stopped to get a few shots of this precious creature.  This was the closest that I got to the fawn.  Once we got in the car, we saw the mother deer resting across the road.

In case you were wondering, if you see a fawn in the woods that looks alone, don’t touch it.  The mother will return, the fawn is not abandoned, and the fawn is safe.  Fawns do not have a scent that predators can smell, and they remain still.
